  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I block Skype on Mac?",
  "response": "To block Skype on a Mac, you have several options. Let's go through a step-by-step approach to achieve this:\n\n1. Uninstall Skype:\n   The simplest way to block Skype is to uninstall it. However, this method may not be suitable if you need to block Skype for other users on the same Mac.\n\n2. Use parental controls:\n   macOS has built-in parental controls that can be used to block specific applications, including Skype.\n\n3. Modify hosts file:\n   You can block Skype's server connections by editing the hosts file.\n\n4. Use third-party firewall software:\n   Some firewall applications allow you to block specific applications from accessing the internet.\n\nLet's focus on the most effective method for blocking Skype for all users on the Mac: modifying the hosts file. Here's how to do it:\n\n1. Open Terminal:\n   You can find Terminal in Applications > Utilities, or use Spotlight (Cmd + Space) and search for \"Terminal\".\n\n2. Edit the hosts file:\n   Use the following command to open the hosts file in a text editor:\n\n   ```\n   sudo nano /etc/hosts\n   ```\n\n   You'll be prompted for your administrator password.\n\n3. Add Skype server entries:\n   At the end of the file, add the following lines to block Skype's servers:\n\n   ```\n   127.0.0.1 skype.com\n   127.0.0.1 go.skype.com\n   127.0.0.1 download.skype.com\n   127.0.0.1 apps.skype.com\n   127.0.0.1 login.skype.com\n   127.0.0.1 api.skype.com\n   127.0.0.1 static.skype.com\n   127.0.0.1 s.gateway.messenger.live.com\n   ```\n\n4. Save and exit:\n   Press Ctrl + O to save, then Ctrl + X to exit the editor.\n\n5. Flush DNS cache:\n   To ensure the changes take effect immediately, flush the DNS cache with:\n\n   ```\n   sudo killall -HUP mDNSResponder\n   ```\n\nThis method will prevent Skype from connecting to its servers, effectively blocking the application from functioning properly.\n\nNote that Microsoft may change Skype's server addresses, so you might need to update this list periodically. Also, be aware that modifying system files like the hosts file can have unintended consequences if not done carefully.\n\nIf you need to unblock Skype in the future, simply remove the lines you added from the hosts file using the same method.",
